\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ their asherim. He went back to [the Torah portion] (Deut. 16:18): Judges and law enforcing 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ agents, and found written (verse 21): You shall not plant an asherah. Then he rejoiced that he had 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ abolished them. He also saw written there: Judges and law enforcing agents you shall appoint for 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ yourself, and immediately he appointed judges, strong ones. \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ in all the fortified cities of Judah, for 
