\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ agony. This is written in the continuous present tense, i.e., not all at once but continuously being 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ crushed by illnesses, and then dying. An example is (Jer. 16:4): Dying of \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ (ממותי)\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  sicknesses they shall 
