\deflang1033\pard\par\plain\par\ql \par\ql \lang1033\ltrch\f6\fs40\b\i0\ul0\cf6\cb14\ 7\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ For the wicked Athaliahher sons had breached\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  He had to say this because Solomon had built it 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ as a new sturdy edifice. Only 125 years elapsed from the time that Solomon built it until the days of 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ Joash and it was already breached. Had Athaliah and her sons not breached it, it would have continued 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ to endure, for more than 200 years elapsed from Joash to Josiah and they did not have to repair it until 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ Josiah, although Joash did not make it new as it was originally. One hundred and twenty-five years 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ elapsed from the completion of the Temple until Joash. How so? Solomon reigned 40 years, and in the 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ fourth year of his reign he commenced to build it. It took 7 years to build, totaling 10 years, leaving 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ him 30. Rehoboam reigned 17, totaling 47; Abijah 3, totaling 50; Asa 41, totaling 91; Jehoshaphat 25, 
